abstract: The Federal Communications Commission is examining a recent decision by Apple to reject a program that Google had developed for the iPhone.
snippet: The Federal Communications Commission is examining a recent decision by Apple to reject a program that Google had developed for the iPhone.
lead_paragraph: The Federal Communications Commission is examining a recent decision by Apple to reject an iPhone application developed by Google. On Friday, the commission sent letters to executives at Apple, Google and AT&T, which is the exclusive carrier for the iPhone in the United States, saying it was “interested in a more complete understanding of this situation.”

headline.main: F.C.C. Looking Into Rejection of Google App for iPhone
headline.print_headline: F.C.C. Looking Into Rejection of Google App for iPhone
